title: @ops.RegisterShape('ApproxMatch') AttributeError: module 'tensorflow.python.framework.ops' has no attribute 'RegisterShape'
body:
The problem itself is quite clear. Regardless the version of TF, Cuda, and the rest, and also in the most updated ones, I keep getting this error. From my understanding, I assume that this error should pop up with updated versions of tensorflow and etc, but I get it in all the tries I have done no matter what. 
I see this can be done [registering the operations via C++](https://www.tensorflow.org/guide/create_op ), with the proper implementation of `SetShapeFn`, but I don't understand how and what parameters to make it. It's strange that I haven't found any implementation to fix this and I am having trouble doing it as well. 
Any ideas?
